# DRAFT FOR ANALYST REVIEW — CVE-2026-0284
#
# Target: Palo Alto Networks PAN-OS — XML Injection in Large Scale VPN (LSVPN)
#
# SEVERITY DISCREPANCY — Analysts must review before deployment:
#   [1] NVD scores this CVSS 9.9 (CRITICAL)
#   [3] CVE.org (CNA-published, CVSS v4.0) scores this 4.7 (MEDIUM)
#   These scores differ substantially. The CNA (Palo Alto Networks) assigned
#   the lower score via their own advisory [2], which lists urgency MODERATE
#   and exploit maturity UNREPORTED. Analysts should weigh both before
#   prioritising response.
#
# PoC status: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the CVE/advisory
#   description only. [2] lists exploit maturity as UNREPORTED.
#
# PCAP status: No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this
#   pipeline — this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
#
# Pattern confidence: LOW.
#   The rule targets HTTP/HTTPS traffic toward PAN-OS LSVPN endpoints,
#   looking for common XML injection sequences (injected tag delimiters and
#   entity references) in request bodies. PAN-OS LSVPN satellite
#   communication typically uses HTTPS on port 443; the specific URI path
#   and parameter names for the vulnerable LSVPN input are NOT confirmed in
#   available public sources [1][2][3]. The content matches below are
#   generic XML injection indicators and MUST be validated against real
#   PAN-OS LSVPN traffic by an analyst before any enforcement action is
#   considered. High false-positive risk against any XML-bearing traffic.
#
alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET $HTTP_PORTS (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-0284 PAN-OS LSVPN XML injection attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.method; content:"POST";
  http.uri; content:"/ssl-vpn/"; nocase;
  http.request_body;
  pcre:"/(?:<[^>]*>.*<\/[^>]*>|&#x?[0-9a-fA-F]+;|%3C[^%]*%3E|<!\[CDATA\[)/i";
  threshold:type limit, track by_src, count 3, seconds 60;
  reference:cve,2026-0284;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-recon; sid:9000084; rev:1; )

